    The payout can be specified through a number of combinations, e.g. by associating several interest rate payouts to specify an interest rate swap, or a credit default and an interest rate payout to specify a credit default swap. The implied product is inferred by the isProduct CDM artefact. Each of the payout classes have an associated rosettaKeyValue which can be referenced by implementers as part of their grossCahflow attribute in the Transfer class, but establishing a lineage between this computed cashflow and the originating payout, when applicable.
